headline: AMD, Cisco and Saudi's Humain launch AI joint venture, land first major customer
summary: SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) -Advanced Micro Devices, Cisco Systems and Saudi Arabian artificial intelligence startup Humain are forming a joint venture to build data centers in the Middle ​East and have landed their first customer, CEOs at the three companies told Reuters in an interview on ‌Tuesday.  The yet-to-be-named joint venture will kick off with a 100-megawatt data center project in Saudi Arabia - the computing capacity of ‌which Humain has contracted to supply generative video startup Luma AI, according to Humain CEO Tareq Amin.

headline: Compal Showcases High-Density Liquid-Cooled AI Servers at SC25, Powered by AMD EPYC™ Processors and AMD Instinct ™ GPUs for Next-Generation Sustainable Computing
summary: Compal Electronics (Compal; Ticker: 2324.TW) make a strong appearance at Supercomputing 2025 (SC25), held from November 17–20, 2025, unveiling its latest lineup of AI and high-performance computing (HPC) servers. Highlight products include the SG720-2A / OG720-2A and SG223-2A-I, showcasing Compal's innovation in liquid-cooling integration solutions that enable data centers to achieve new levels of performance, efficiency, and sustainability.

headline: AMD, Intel and TSMC brace for Nvidia earnings: trending stocks
summary: Stocks of chipmakers including AMD (AMD), Intel (INTC) and TSMC (TSM, TSMC.BA) waver as markets hold their breath ahead of Nvidia (NVDA)'s earnings report. Cloudflare (NET) ticks up despite a widespread outage. Tesla (TSLA) challenger Xiaomi (1810.HK, XIACY, XIACF, 3CP.F, 1810N.MX) sees shares plummet - even as its EV arm turns an operating profit for the first time. Following a crisis sparked by an accounting error in its North American division, British high-street retailer WH Smith (SMWH.L) pushes for a turnaround. And Doordash (DASH) delivers some news - including a new partnership. For more live coverage of the markets, watch the full episode of Market Sunrise and visit Yahoo Finance.
